-- Mozambique, Portugal Agree to Start Lender to Fund Development Projects
-- Fred Katerere
-- 2010-06-14T17:46:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/mozambique-portugal-agree-to-start-lender-to-fund-development-projects.html

          
          
             Mozambique and Portugal agreed to
start a bank that will fund development projects in the southern
African country, Portuguese Finance Minister Fernando Teixeira
dos Santos said.  
 Banco Nacional de Investmentos will have capital of $500
million with funding from the Mozambican Treasury and Caixa
Geral de Depositos SA of Portugal, Teixeira dos Santos told
reporters in the capital, Maputo, today.  
 It will be headed by former Mozambique central bank
Governor Adelaine Maleilane and based in Maputo, Mozambique
Finance Minister Manuel Chang said.  
